==English==

===Etymology===
Blend of English ''big'' and English ''miniature''; from the ''Lord of the Rings'' movies

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''bigature''' (''plural'' '''bigatures''')
[big' uh churr]

# (''usually Film-making'') An object that is technically a miniature, but still is large (such as the Crane model of the ''Matrix'' trilogy).

